I wasn't even thinking of mounting the heater core in the front.------

The heater box, with the fan, mounted in the rear would be more than
sufficient.

These things put out allot of heat, and used in conjunction with the
forced air set-up that's already there---Break out your Hawaiian shirt
and the shorts------It's going to be warm, real warm.

No srtain on the pump either--- running the oil through an oil line, and
oil cooler isn't going to do zip----

Later,

Terry



 
