From: Corbett.Messa(-at-)gefanuc.com 


How long do you think that you could plumb the oil lines before you put
a strain on the oil pump? What if you mounted the oil cooler under the
rear seat in a Westy. Build some type or box around it and added a fan.
This would help with the passengers in the cabin getting warm. 
Corbett 
Remote oil coolers would require looong oil lines in a bus application.
The ones in Beetles only go through the package shelf floor and the
cooler is mounted there, behind the rear seat. Even at that, I think
there'd be some oil pressure drop; and even more if you're gonna plumb
it all the way to the driver in a bus...I'd bet you'd be putting quite a
strain on the oil pump... 
Tony in NJ
